cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with visual navigation, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves path planning and control, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The formulation proposed in the paper is learned from data, which suggests the involvement of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves goal-driven navigation, which involves decision making and planning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves closed-loop control, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
